        </div>

        <div class="wrap" data-focus="email">
            <section id="main" role="main">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="columns eight">
                        <div class="module">
                            <section class="intro">
                                <p>President Obama has announced the biggest steps to fight climate change that any president has ever taken. He's not waiting around for climate deniers in Congress who won't even acknowledge the scientific fact of climate change to face reality in order to act&mdash;he's taking bold steps forward.</p>
                            </section>
                            <section class="four-things">
                                <h3>Four things you can do to get started today</h3>
                                <article class="one">
                                    <h4>Sign up to volunteer</h4>
                                    <p>Take the next step and hold your legislator accountable.</p>
                                    <p style="text-align:center"><a class="button green" href="https://my.barackobama.com/page/s/climate-page-petition">ADD YOUR NAME</a></p>
                                </article>
                                <article class="two">
                                    <h4>Spread the word</h4>
                                    <p>Make sure your friends and family know that President Obama is taking bold action to fight climate change. Share this graphic on Facebook today.</p>
                                    <p class="fbImg"><a href="http://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https://www.facebook.com/photo.php?fbid=10151655415581749&set=a.53081056748.66806.6815841748&type=1&theater" title="share" ><img src="https://secure.assets.bostatic.com/frontend/projects/i-will/img/share.jpg" alt="share on Facebook"></a></p>
                                    <p class="btn-cont"><a href="http://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https://www.facebook.com/photo.php?fbid=10151655415581749&set=a.53081056748.66806.6815841748&type=1&theater" title="Share" class="button green">Share</a></p>
                                </article>
                                <article class="three">
                                    <h4>Call out a climate denier</h4>
                                    <p>Check out our list of known climate deniers in Congress-elected officials who refuse to even acknowledge the science behind climate change&mdash;and call them out on Twitter.</p>
                                    <p class="btn-cont"><a href="http://www.barackobama.com/climate-deniers" target="blank" class="button green">Call them out</a></p>
                                </article>
                                <article class="four">
                                    <h4>Help your community switch to clean energy</h4>
                                    <p>This summer, OFA volunteers across the country will be taking steps to switch their communities to clean energy. Find out how you can help.</p>
                                    <p class="btn-cont"><a href="https://my.barackobama.com/page/s/i-will-climate-events" target="blank" class="button green">Learn more</a></p>
                                </article>
                            </section>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="columns four sidebar">
                        <ul>
                            <li class="heading"><p>The President's plan to combat climate change:</p></li>
                            <li class="odd"><p>Create the first-ever EPA limits on how much carbon pollution U.S. power plants can create</p></li>
                            <li class="even"><p>Double the production of clean energy in the U.S. by 2020</p></li>
                            <li class="odd"><p>Lead the international community to address global climate change</p></li>
                            <li class="even"><p>Prepare the U.S. for the impacts of climate change</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
